{
  "texts": [
    "See, e.g., Beutel et al., 2023; Guerreiro et al., 2023; Bang et al., 2023).",
    "Current LLM systems do not implement forms of active learning and autonomous engagement with world's affordances.",
    "Even if the system could be able to recover facts about the world's structure, the recovered facts are explicitly based on the 4E human experience, hence the depiction of LLMs as \"stochastic parrots\", due to their pattern-matching approach to language detailed above (Bender et al., 2021).",
    "2 Others consider LLMs only an outward display of intelligence: similarly to Searle's \"Chinese Room\", they give the impression of comprehending only because they can match incoming input-symbols with specific outputsymbols (Searle, 1980).",
    "Obviously, it is not possible to say that disembodied entities such as LLMs could never achieve understanding or agency in some sense."
  ]
}